# The last 3 columns in this dataset are very important. They are casual, registered, and count (cnt). People who register with the service can get discounts and some benefits, placing 
# them in the registered column - but bikes can be rented without registering, which is the casual column.
# The cnt column is the sum of both the casual and registered columns.
# I am already taking note that there are more registered riders than casual riders.

# Calucating summary statistics to begin making sense of the data 

print(hour['cnt'].median())
142.0
