# When 0, not a holiday, when 1, it is a holiday
# Non-holidays seem to have higher riderships across seasons, for the most part. The exception would be the summer, but the difference is not significant

# I wanted to see the difference in mean/average ridership across both years in the dataset by weekday ( 0 = Monday) 
print(hour.groupby(['yr', 'weekday'])['cnt'].mean())
               
