## Visualizing Data with Matplotlib
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Plot your data early and often 

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,6))
ax.scatter(x = hour['instant'], y = hour['cnt'])
<matplotlib.collections.PathCollection object at 0x1147aadb0>
plt.show()

# The graph clearly shows what I noticed above - average ridership increased significantly from 2011 to 2012. It also shows a seasonal trend.

